  				<tr>
  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table width=75% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>  <tr>
    <td width='100%' align='left' valign='top' bgcolor='#0E024D' colspan=5 class='spti2'>NECROMANCER FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db2' colspan=2>Click <a href=faq.asp?Action=SubmitQ>Here</a> To Submit A Frequently Asked Question<hr size='1'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>For Necromancer Pets, Which Delay is in effect?  The delay of the weapon or the delay of the pet? At lower levels (non-dual wield) is it better to equip a high damage/high delay weapon (because pet delay is used) or a normal damage/low delay weapon (because weaon delay is used)?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>After a recent patch, the damage and delay of each classes pet were made a set value for each level, so the delay and damage will not change if you give them a weapon. However, if you give your pet a weapon with a proc, that proc will still go off if the pet uses it. Lastly, at higher levels, giving a pet two weapons enables it to dual wield.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Is being an evil necromancer really difficult due to the bad faction with so many npc's and towns?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Not really, at first it may seem that way and more so on newer servers where dealing with npcs is more common but in later levels being evil can be a great advantage where one can hunt anything without having to worry about the faction loss.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Does charisma ever affect the resist rate or duration on the fear line of spells?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>No.  Charisma is not a saving throw stat for Fear spells.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>If I duel another player will my fear spell work on them like an NPC? </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Yes.  Fear spells do not work on PvP servers, but in duel environments there is no restriction in using the spell.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Can a Necromancer levitate without the spellbook before lvl.35,or can a Necro even levitate</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>No, but they can cast a spell called Dead Man Floating, which gives the levitate effect, and also see invis, enduring breath, and an added poison resist.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>At what level will a Necromancer pet be able to dual weild?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Necromancer pets can often wield from Level 24 up, and reliably from Level 29 and up.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Can a Necromancer combine words for spells which are not able to cast?  For example if you had the words for a level 20 spell and you were only 18 would the words automatically vaporize or would you have the possibility of creating a spell you could put in the bank and use when you hit level 20?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>You certainly can create spells before you can scribe them.  Research is not limited by level, so you coul dtheoretically raise your skill high enough to make Level 49 spells at Level 16, and simply scribe them as you reach higher levels.<P></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>When equiping your a pet that has dual wield capability, does the type of weapon matter?  I recall Verant saying, after the weapon delay patch, that there was a problem with dual wield.

</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>It used to be the case that if two identical weapons (i.e. two fine steel daggers) were given to a pet, it would not activate dual wield.  However, this has now been changed and you <u>can</u> give any two one handed weapons to your pet with no effect on the speed of the attacks.  Be careful when using weapons which are restricted to a particular melee slot.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>I asked yesterday if you can use the words for spells which you cannot access yet to make spells and store them into bank to scroll in later?  For example, you are a level 18 necro who has the base words for a level 20 spell.  Can you place the words in the book of Dark Bindings and create a level 20 spell even though you cannot cast it now?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>You certainly can.  Research is also not capped per level so you could theoretically practice up to, and then make, level 49 spells at level 16.  You simply cannot scribe the scrolls you make into your spell book.<P>
You can access our Necromancer Research section <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/research/Necromancer/'><b>here</b></a>.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Please explain magic specialization.  I need to know if I can choose the schools of magic that I specialize in, or is that determined by which school reaches the 50th skill level first?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Everything you need to know about specialization can be found in our Specialization guide located
<a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/misc/pages/special.asp'><b>here</b></a>.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Is it possible to recover a weapon that is given to a pet?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>No.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db' colspan=2 align=right></td>
  </tr>
